result.name: M Garden Vegetarian

reviews.text: I'm not vegetarian but my sister is, so we decided to come to this restaurant where she and her vegetarian friends go.  The food was very tasty and ingredients were high quality.    Service is reasonably quick.  Place is quite noisy for conversation but not much more than typical restaurants in Hong Kong.  The place was quite busy and tables filled up after 7:30pm, so suggest making reservations if you don't want to be disappointed.
simple  authentic food, sichuan spicy chicken must try..

Mandatory $12 for tea and 10% service charge to piss you off !! 
Otherwise a 10/10 for the quality of food.

The waitress told me they ran out of tissue paper  Ha ha! 

Next time I would rather go to the Veggie Food on the other side of the street with same quality and no mandatory tea and service charge

Baked avocado 🥑 was a little overrated. The sauce on top of the avocado tastes somewhat like a mayo dressing 🤮 which does not go very well with the avocado!
The veggie chicken appetiser and veggie fish in a steam pot were delicious. 
Steam egg white with tofu was super good. 😋
Fried rice was fairly good. The dish could have been hotter.
Service was ok, partly because we expected very little from the waiters.
In a good way, we were basically undisturbed for 2 hours.

Bad, Very bad. Though completely vegan hotel, they have given their menu items names as non-veg, which means you don’t understand what the hell it is. Staff not helpful as well. They will put a fruit and tea default in your bill worth almost 30hk $.

result.name: 常悅素食

reviews.text: 已經食過好多次，從不令人失望。菜式多選擇，味道好。午餐有點心供應，坐得舒適。晚市人多，但無限制用膳時間。店員招呼好，地點佳。
交通方便，人多好迫。價錢5平。
午飯時間與同事們到此店試食。這裡的小菜及主食不算太多，而且沒有鹵味，但卻有幾項特色食品(其他素食店沒有的)。食物的味道及質素相當不錯，特色小食亦非常突出。雖然價格不低，但以食物質素及特色來計算，依然是吸引的，我本人樂意推薦。
地方不算寬敞，是飲茶中菜素食館， 有很多點心， 下午2:30是特價時間。
